@startuml SD_03_GoogleOAuth
' ============================================================
' SEQUENCE DIAGRAM - Google OAuth 2.0 Login
' FR-03: Google Sign-in → Auto-create User → Session
' ============================================================

title **SD-03: Google OAuth 2.0 Login\n(Google Sign-in → Session)**

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam maxmessagesize 200
skinparam sequence {
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #E3F2FD
    ParticipantBorderColor #1565C0
    ArrowColor #1565C0
}

actor "Guest" as User #LightGreen
participant "Browser\n(JSP)" as Browser #LightYellow
participant "GoogleAuthServlet\n(Controller)" as Auth #E3F2FD
participant "GoogleCallbackServlet\n(Callback)" as Callback #E3F2FD
participant "GoogleOAuthService" as Service #E8F5E9
participant "UserService" as UserSvc #E8F5E9
participant "UserDAO" as DAO #FFF3E0
box "External" #F5F5F5
    participant "Google\nOAuth 2.0" as Google #FFCDD2
end box
database "SQL Server" as DB #F3E5F5

== Step 1: Initiate Google Login ==

User -> Browser: Click "Sign in with Google"
Browser -> Auth: GET /auth/google
activate Auth

Auth -> Auth: Generate state token:\nstate = UUID.randomUUID()\nsession.setAttribute(\n  "oauth_state", state)

Auth -> Auth: Build Auth URL:\nhttps://accounts.google.com/\no/oauth2/v2/auth?\nclient_id={CLIENT_ID}\n&redirect_uri={CALLBACK_URL}\n&response_type=code\n&scope=openid email profile\n&state={state}

Auth --> Browser: Redirect → Google Auth URL
deactivate Auth

== Step 2: Google Authentication ==

Browser -> Google: Redirect to Google Login
activate Google
Google --> User: Display Google\naccount selection screen
User -> Google: Select account +\nGrant permissions
Google -> Google: Validate credentials
Google --> Browser: Redirect →\n{CALLBACK_URL}?\ncode={auth_code}\n&state={state}
deactivate Google

== Step 3: Handle Callback ==

Browser -> Callback: GET /auth/google/callback\n?code={auth_code}\n&state={state}
activate Callback

' --- CSRF Verification ---
Callback -> Callback: Validate state:\nsession.state == param.state?

alt #FFE0E0 State Mismatch (CSRF attack)
    Callback --> Browser: Redirect → /login\n?error=invalid_state
    Browser --> User: ❌ Login failed\n(security error)
else #E8F5E9 State Valid

    ' --- Exchange Code for Tokens ---
    Callback -> Service: exchangeCodeForTokens(code)
    activate Service
    Service -> Google: POST /token\n{code, client_id,\nclient_secret,\nredirect_uri,\ngrant_type=authorization_code}
    activate Google
    Google --> Service: {\n  access_token: "ya29...",\n  id_token: "eyJ...",\n  refresh_token: "1//...",\n  expires_in: 3600\n}
    deactivate Google

    ' --- Get User Info ---
    Service -> Google: GET /userinfo\nAuthorization: Bearer {access_token}
    activate Google
    Google --> Service: {\n  sub: "118234567890",\n  email: "user@gmail.com",\n  name: "Nguyen Van A",\n  picture: "https://...photo.jpg",\n  email_verified: true\n}
    deactivate Google

    Service --> Callback: GoogleUserInfo
    deactivate Service

    ' --- Find or Create User ---
    Callback -> UserSvc: findOrCreateOAuthUser(\ngoogleUserInfo)
    activate UserSvc

    UserSvc -> DAO: findByEmail(email)
    activate DAO
    DAO -> DB: SELECT * FROM Users\nWHERE email = ?
    activate DB
    DB --> DAO: User or null
    deactivate DB
    DAO --> UserSvc: result
    deactivate DAO

    alt User Not Found (new user)
        UserSvc -> DAO: create(User)
        activate DAO
        DAO -> DB: INSERT INTO Users (\n  userId=NEWID(), email,\n  fullName, avatar=picture,\n  role='customer',\n  oauthUser=1,\n  oauthProvider='google',\n  oauthId=sub, password=NULL,\n  isActive=1, createdAt\n)
        activate DB
        DB --> DAO: new userId
        deactivate DB
        DAO --> UserSvc: New User
        deactivate DAO
    else User Exists
        UserSvc -> UserSvc: Check oauthUser flag:\nif oauthUser=false →\nuser registered via email,\nlink Google account
        UserSvc -> DAO: updateOAuth(userId,\noauthProvider, oauthId)
        activate DAO
        DAO -> DB: UPDATE Users SET\noauthUser=1,\noauthProvider='google',\noauthId=?\nWHERE userId=?
        activate DB
        DB --> DAO: Updated
        deactivate DB
        DAO --> UserSvc: Updated User
        deactivate DAO
    end

    UserSvc --> Callback: User
    deactivate UserSvc

    ' --- Create Session ---
    Callback -> Callback: session.setAttribute("user", user)\nsession.setAttribute("role", role)

    Callback -> DB: INSERT INTO ActivityLogs\n(action='OAUTH_LOGIN',\ndetails='google', userId)

    Callback --> Browser: Redirect → /\n+ flash: "Google login\nsuccessful!"
    deactivate Callback
    Browser --> User: ✅ Login successful,\nredirect to homepage
end

@enduml
